petitor%20Bluesky%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Like%20worried%20liberals%20threatening%20to%20decamp%20for%20Canada%20or%20Europe%2C%20ex-Xers%20are%20heading%20for%20bluer%20pastures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20the%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-migration-shows-no-signs-of-slowing-following-musks-takeover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emass%20migration%3C%2Fa%3E%20away%20from%20the%20site%20formerly%20known%20as%20Twitter.%20But%20this%20one%20included%20a%20lot%20of%20elite%20tastemakers.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20writers%2C%20politicians%2C%20artists%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Emily%20Liu%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%20and%20Bluesky%20spokesperson.%20%26quot%3BWe%20had%20a%20lot%20of%20Swifties.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20anyone%20who%20has%20ever%20packed%20up%20a%20U-Haul%20knows%2C%20the%20problem%20with%20moving%20is%20what%20to%20do%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-x-boomer-inheritance-stuff-house-collectibles-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eall%20your%20old%20stuff%3C%2Fa%3E.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESocial%20networks%20come%20and%20go%2C%20and%20none%20has%20ever%20made%20it%20easy%20%E2%80%94%20or%20even%20possible%20%E2%80%94%20to%20bring%20your%20old%20content%20to%20the%20new%20place.%20Even%20Bluesky%2C%20founded%20in%20part%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20a%20user's%20content%20belongs%20to%20them%20and%20not%20the%20company%2C%20doesn't%20offer%20that%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20Nicolas%20Castellani%20and%20Amos%20da%20Silva%20Bezerra%20come%20in.%20Their%20Brazilian%20startup%2C%20BlueArk%2C%20is%20essentially%20operating%20as%20a%20moving%20company%20for%20Twitter%20expats.%20They've%20only%20been%20in%20business%20a%20month%2C%20yet%20they've%20already%20helped%20thousands%20of%20people%20move%20their%20old%20tweets%20from%20X%20to%20Bluesky%20%E2%80%94%20a%20millions%20of%20posts%2C%20representing%202%20terabytes%20worth%20of%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECastellani%2C%20a%20software%20engineer%2C%20and%20Bezerra%2C%20a%20communications%20student%2C%20hit%20on%20the%20idea%20back%20in%20September%2C%20when%20X%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbluesky-social-media-platform-millions-users-x-banned-brazil-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebriefly%20banned%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20their%20native%20Brazil.%20The%20couple%20had%20chronicled%20their%20romance%20on%20the%20platform%2C%20and%20they%20hated%20the%20idea%20of%20losing%20those%20memories%20when%20they%20moved%20to%20Bluesky.%20So%20they%20came%20up%20with%20a%20way%20to%20scrape%20their%20X%20accounts%20and%20export%20the%20tweets%20to%20the%20rival%20social%20network.%20And%20thanks%20to%20Bluesky's%20unusually%20open%20tech%2C%20the%20tweets%20would%20retain%20their%20original%20date%20stamps%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20they%20predated%20Bluesky's%20opening%20in%202022.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20Castellani%20and%20Bezerra%20could%20give%20Bluesky%20something%20it%20didn't%20have%3A%20a%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20things%20we%20actually%20wanted%20to%20do%20is%20make%20it%20seem%20like%20a%20person%2C%20that%20all%20of%20us%2C%20were%20actually%20on%20Bluesky%20the%20whole%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Bezerra%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20want%20to%20pretend%20that%20Twitter%20doesn't%20exist.%20But%20we%20want%20to%20give%20the%20sensation%20that%20you've%20been%20on%20Bluesky%20for%20a%20long%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20churn%20of%20people%20leaving%20Twitter%20after%20Musk%20bought%20the%20company%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecreated%20an%20opening%20for%20rivals%20like%20Bluesky%2C%20Mastodon%2C%20and%20Meta's%20Threads.%20But%20while%20Mastodon%20felt%20technically%20difficult%20and%20Threads%20felt%20engagement-baiting%2C%20Bluesky%20opted%20for%20creating%20an%20experience%20that's%20fun%20and%20friendly.%20Its%20interface%20is%20Twitter-like%20to%20the%20point%20of%20flattery%2C%20but%20unlike%20X%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20shape%20the%20experience%20to%20reflect%20your%20own%20needs%20and%20preferences.%20Block%20someone%20on%20Bluesky%20and%20it's%20%26quot%3Bnuclear%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20they%20don't%20see%20you%20anymore%2C%20or%20anything%20referring%20to%20you%2C%20and%20you%20don't%20see%20them.%20You%20can%20retroactively%20stop%20someone%20from%20embedding%20one%20of%20your%20posts%20in%20one%20of%20theirs%2C%20to%20short-circuit%20the%20kind%20of%20mass%20harassment%20campaigns%20that%20have%20become%20common%20on%20X.%20And%20Bluesky%20has%20promised%20never%20to%20use%20your%20posts%20to%20train%20AI%20bots%20%E2%80%94%20something%20X%20just%20changed%20its%20terms%20of%20service%20to%20permit.%20Over%20the%20past%20three%20months%2C%20Bluesky%20has%20added%2013%20million%20users%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20now%20the%20No.%201%20social%20network%20on%20many%20app%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBezerra%20and%20Castellani%20aim%20to%20capitalize%20on%20Bluesky's%20feel-good%20vibe.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20thing%20we%20want%20to%20sell%2C%26quot%3B%20Castellani%20says.%20When%20the%20couple%20first%20started%20dating%2C%20they%20watched%20the%20TV%20show%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-good-place-finale-series-changed-my-life-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Good%20Place%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20when%20they%20founded%20BlueArk%2C%20they%20discovered%20that%20lots%20of%20people%20called%20X%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Bad%20Place%26quot%3B%20and%20Bluesky%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Good%20Place.%26quot%3B%20Now%2C%20given%20Musk's%20full-on%20bromance%20with%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20they're%20racing%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20demand%3A%20Given%20the%20backlog%20of%20requests%2C%20full%20ports%20are%20taking%20nearly%20two%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20lot%20of%20folks%2C%20it's%20worth%20the%20wait.%20David%20Shiffman%2C%20a%20marine%20biologist%2C%20was%20a%20self-proclaimed%20%26quot%3Bpower%20user%26quot%3B%20on%20Twitter%20before%20it%20devolved%20into%20what%20he%20sees%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bcesspool%20of%20bigotry%20and%20pseudoscience%20and%20conspiracy%20theory.%26quot%3B%20So%20Shiffman%20used%20BlueArk%20to%20move%20his%20300%2C000%20tweets%20over%20to%20Bluesky.%20%26quot%3BI%20jumped%20at%20the%20chance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20like%20a%20lifeboat%20that%20lets%20me%20carry%20some%20of%20my%20most%20prized%20possessions%20off%20the%20sinking%20ship.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20itself%20is%20easy.%20The%20BlueArk%20website%20asks%20for%20your%20Bluesky%20account%20and%20password%2C%20and%20your%20Twitter%20ID.%20Then%20the%20team%20verifies%20your%20identity%20in%20both%20places.%20They%20charge%20a%20bit%20for%20the%20Twitter%20scrape%20and%20their%20time%3B%20moving%20my%20tens%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethousands%20of%20tweets%2C%20dating%20back%20to%202009%2C%20cost%20about%20%2417.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20technical%20perspective%2C%20that's%20possible%20only%20because%20of%20Bluesky's%20open%20tech.%20Its%20%26quot%3BAT%20Protocol%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20says%2C%20is%20designed%20for%20%26quot%3Baccount%20portability%26quot%3B%20going%20forward.%20%26quot%3BWe%20know%20lots%20of%20people%20are%20importing%20their%20old%20posts%2C%20and%20we're%20excited%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Liu%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20Bluesky's%20developers%20are%20also%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20ways%20people%20might%20try%20to%20cheat%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20by%20backdating%20an%20old%20tweet%20to%20create%20misinformation.%20You%20don't%20want%20people%20implanting%20false%20memories%20into%20the%20new%20ecosystem.%20A%20friendly%20developer%20actually%20sent%20Bluesky%20an%20example%20of%20what%20could%20go%20wrong%3A%20a%20faked%20Bluesky%20post%20with%20a%20hacked%20time%20stamp%20of%20September%2011%2C%202001.%20It%20read%3A%20%26quot%3BSure%20hope%20nothing%20bad%20happens%20today!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20honest%2C%20I've%20found%20it%20a%20bit%20weird%20to%20see%20my%20old%20tweets%20in%20my%20new%20home.%20The%20other%20day%2C%20someone%20threw%20a%20Bluesky%20like%20at%20a%20tweet%20I%20wrote%20in%202013.%20To%20fix%20that%20%E2%80%94%20and%20to%20minimize%20the%20potential%20for%20tampering%20with%20old%20tweets%20%E2%80%94%20Bluesky%20is%20planning%20to%20label%20posts%20that%20are%20moved%20over%20from%20other%20platforms.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20about%20to%20ship%20an%20update%20to%20show%20old%20posts%20that%20are%20imported%20with%20an%20archival%20tag%2C%26quot%3B%20Liu%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20there's%20one%20more%20step%20to%20the%20move.%20Once%20I've%20got%20all%20my%20old%20tweets%20unpacked%20on%20Bluesky%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20head%20back%20over%20to%20X%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fhow-to-delete-all-tweets-on-twitter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etorch%20my%20entire%20archive%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20are%20fleeing%20X%20are%20setting%20up%20that%20process%20to%20happen%20automatically%2C%20to%20make%20sure%20their%20words%20aren't%20the%20property%20of%20a%20transnational%20megacorporation%20with%20ties%20to%20the%20new%20administration%20and%20a%20willingness%20to%20feed%20the%20AI%20beast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20bittersweet%20bonfire.%20Deleting%20your%20back%20catalog%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eon%20Twitter%20also%20disembowels%20whatever%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdigital-dark-ages-internet-history-old-websites-disappearing-link-rot-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econversations%20those%20tweets%20were%20part%20of%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20no%20matter%20how%20you%20feel%20about%20Musk%20and%20X%2C%20that's%20kind%20of%20sad.%20The%20best%20part%20of%20Twitter%20was%20always%20the%20social%20aspect%20of%20the%20network%2C%20the%20way%20it%20brought%20people%20together%20in%20all%20sorts%20of%20delightful%20and%20unexpected%20ways.%20When%20you%20leave%2C%20your%20absence%20leaves%20a%20hole%20in%20the%20relationships%20you%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20have%20some%20mourning%20about%20the%20loss%20of%20the%20conversations%2C%20the%20emergent%20thing%20that%20was%20Twitter%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Joe%20Bak-Coleman%2C%20a%20researcher%20who%20studies%20collective%20behavior%20and%20social%20networks.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20it's%20just%20a%20false%20belief%20%E2%80%94%20that%20parts%20of%20the%20internet%20are%20permanent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20not.%20Like%20so%20many%20others%2C%20I'm%20taking%20my%20tweets%20and%20striking%20out%20for%20new%20territories.%20We%20can%20finally%20carry%20our%20histories%20with%20us.%20But%20the%20internet%20will%20move%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fadam-rogers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAdam%20Rogers%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-helping-people-leave-twitter-bluesky-tweets-perserve-social-media-2024-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1732010641000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F673ba91cfa0140cdd56422c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-helping-people-leave-twitter-bluesky-tweets-perserve-social-media-2024-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20Elon%20Musk%20teams%20up%20with%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20a%20startup%20is%20helping%20users%20move%20their%20old%20tweets%20to%20bluer%20pastures.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22arogers%40businessinsider.com%20(Adam%20Rogers)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business